title: NC Sub-basins (portions of River Basins) Used to Regulate Interbasin Water Transfers between Water Systems
name: NC Sub-basins (portions of River Basins) Used to Regulate Interbasin Water Transfers between Water Systems
description: These are the 38 sub-basins, as defined in North Carolina Statute GS 143-215.22G, that are used by NC DENR's Division of Water Resources to identify when interbasin transfer permits are required. These are not HUCs and they are not the 17 river basins of North Carolina. Each sub-basin is bounded within a river basin boundary, and generally follow HUC subbasin boundaries - but have been modified to follow political boundaries in a few cases.

author.source: Division of Water Resources, NC Department of Environment and Natural Resources
